Instructions for making a new release:

1) git checkout master
2) git clean -d -x -f         # I hope you've commit or stashed everything
                              # you are working on
2) git fetch
3) git rebase origin
4) Edit configure.ac and remove the '-devel' from the line beginning with
   "AC_INIT([pyparted],".  The release version should just be X.Y.Z/
5) git add configure.ac
6) git commit                 # Comment should be 'New version.' or similar.
7) ./bootstrap
8) ./configure
9) make release

Resulting pyparted-X.Y.Z.tar.gz is the release.  'cp -a' this to the pkg
CVS tree and make a new build.  Also need to copy it to the project
download site and make a new version entry in the Trac site.

10) git push
11) git push --tags
12) Edit configure.ac and change the version from X.Y.Z to X.Y.(Z+1)-devel
13) git add configure.ac
14) git commit
15) git push
